<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="799" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d799">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.711/18</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GWE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-09T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your March 9, 11 a.m. Department compliments you upon successfully
                            arranging for censorship in Cuba of all mail in transit by Spanish
                            steamers between Mexico and Spain and vice versa. It is important that
                            this censorship be very carefully performed under direct American
                            control and supervision.</p>
                        <p>Report fully by pouch upon present censorship conditions—how arranged and
                            how functioning and position and work of American officers.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>